Remarks:
Close relationships between populations in the caves Obodska pećina (Rijeka Crnojevića, 
Montenegro
) and Obod (in Hercegovina) were asserted by molecular analysis. Specimens from Dejanova pećina (Bileća) and Vilina pećina (Cernica; both in southeastern 
Bosnia and Herzegovina
) are morphologically similar to the ones mentioned above.
